<font color="#FF0000">A POSITIVE CONTRIBUTION</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jun  3  0:48:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Guys, <br><br>
While all of you are verbally bashing each other, another veterans group, some green beenies (Green Baret types) have been burning up the internet, writing congressmen (and women, I suppose) about an issue that matters.  <br><br>
I've just posted an article out of the Hong Kong Morning Post which shows that the Vietnam War is still causing headlines, and still affecting us.  The UN has just granted refugee status to a group of South Vietnamese &quot;boat people&quot; who have been residing in Hong Kong cames for many years now.  The article is posted on site #57, &quot;Attitudes towards American Vietnamese.&quot;  This means that these people will be free to immigrate to the United States before the changeover in the Hong Kong government.<br><br>
I think we need to get beyond the above &quot;dialogs&quot; and explore what we can now contribute to this world in the present, given our unique perspective from these dialog strings.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


